1
00:00:01,626 --> 00:00:03,211
[Norhana sobbing] <i>Miss,</i>
<i>do you know Jamilah?</i>

2
00:00:03,294 --> 00:00:04,462
[nurse] <i>She's still inside.</i>

3
00:00:05,130 --> 00:00:06,965
- [Jalil] <i>We need to split up.</i>
- I'll go this way.

4
00:00:09,759 --> 00:00:11,803
[Tommy] <i>Leave me behind and save yourself.</i>

5
00:00:11,886 --> 00:00:13,722
<i>I'm just going to be a burden to you.</i>

6
00:00:13,805 --> 00:00:14,931
[Jovi] <i>I'll come back for you.</i>

7
00:00:15,640 --> 00:00:17,100
Think of your brother!

8
00:00:17,183 --> 00:00:19,728
His condition might get worse!

9
00:00:19,811 --> 00:00:21,604
[Lara] <i>I've located Miss Teresa.</i>

10
00:00:21,688 --> 00:00:23,940
[Lara] They have another hostage.
A Muslim girl?

11
00:00:24,023 --> 00:00:26,192
[tense music playing]

12
00:00:26,276 --> 00:00:27,277
[grunts]

13
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:28,862
- Help!
- [Marcus] <i>I have eyes on one suspect.</i>

14
00:00:28,945 --> 00:00:31,364
[Marcus] He's got Jamilah, a nurse.

15
00:00:31,448 --> 00:00:33,783
[Jalil] <i>Reyes, save that hostage.</i>

16
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:35,118
I'll save your mother.

17
00:00:35,201 --> 00:00:37,871
[Marcus] <i>Release her. Fight me instead.</i>

18
00:00:37,954 --> 00:00:40,665
[Jalil] <i>Hostage secured.</i>
<i>Your mother is safe.</i>

19
00:00:42,834 --> 00:00:43,877
- [Jamilah shouts]
- [shouts in pain]

20
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:46,296
[Marcus, in English] <i>Hostage clear.</i>
<i>Target secured.</i>

21
00:00:47,672 --> 00:00:48,548
Are you okay?

22
00:00:48,631 --> 00:00:51,134
I'm just making sure that you're safe.

23
00:00:51,217 --> 00:00:54,137
[tense music playing]

24
00:00:56,973 --> 00:00:59,642
[Marcus] <i>Thank you. You saved my mother.</i>

25
00:00:59,726 --> 00:01:02,395
[Jalil] <i>Thank you, too. For saving my--</i>

26
00:01:03,605 --> 00:01:06,149
<i>For saving our fellow Muslim.</i>
<i>Thank you, Reyes.</i>

27
00:01:17,243 --> 00:01:19,204
[mysterious theme music playing]

28
00:01:34,093 --> 00:01:36,137
[morose music playing]

29
00:01:55,281 --> 00:01:56,449
Jamilah.

30
00:01:56,991 --> 00:01:58,660
- Gracia.
- Are you okay?

31
00:01:59,244 --> 00:02:02,247
I need to check the patients in bed 6.

32
00:02:02,330 --> 00:02:05,333
If you need someone
to talk to, I'm right here.

33
00:02:08,086 --> 00:02:09,337
Thank you.

34
00:02:10,296 --> 00:02:11,881
Go check on the patients.

35
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:13,925
The life of a nurse.

36
00:02:14,008 --> 00:02:15,343
No trauma leave.

37
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:19,097
We dreamed of this, remember?

38
00:02:21,224 --> 00:02:23,184
You should go. Thanks again.

39
00:02:26,354 --> 00:02:27,647
[sighs]

40
00:02:30,692 --> 00:02:32,652
[morose music continues]

41
00:02:42,871 --> 00:02:44,581
Jamliah, how are you holding up?

42
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:47,542
Did those jerks hurt you?

43
00:02:48,167 --> 00:02:49,168
Um…

44
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:51,671
I'm fine.

45
00:02:52,338 --> 00:02:54,465
[breathes deeply]

46
00:02:54,549 --> 00:02:56,301
Your son came to my rescue.

47
00:02:56,384 --> 00:02:57,969
That's good to know.

48
00:03:00,597 --> 00:03:02,682
Honestly, Doctor…

49
00:03:06,769 --> 00:03:08,605
I'm still angry with your son.

50
00:03:08,688 --> 00:03:10,732
[melancholic music playing]

51
00:03:12,984 --> 00:03:15,445
I don't know how I can forgive him

52
00:03:15,528 --> 00:03:17,572
after what he did to my father.

53
00:03:20,158 --> 00:03:22,118
Including our neighbors.

54
00:03:32,670 --> 00:03:33,838
[exhales heavily]

55
00:03:37,842 --> 00:03:39,510
‪[deep breath]

56
00:03:39,594 --> 00:03:40,678
But…

57
00:03:42,597 --> 00:03:45,350
I know I should be grateful to him.

58
00:03:48,478 --> 00:03:50,563
Because he saved my life.

59
00:03:51,439 --> 00:03:53,024
I understand you, Jamilah.

60
00:03:54,317 --> 00:03:57,278
We all have a mission in life.

61
00:03:57,362 --> 00:04:01,199
For us, our mission is to save lives.

62
00:04:01,699 --> 00:04:04,619
Meanwhile, my son's mission is…

63
00:04:05,745 --> 00:04:07,372
to fulfill his duty.

64
00:04:08,206 --> 00:04:09,499
It just so happened

65
00:04:09,582 --> 00:04:12,919
that it was the mission
he was given at the time.

66
00:04:13,002 --> 00:04:14,879
[camera shutter clicking]

67
00:04:14,963 --> 00:04:18,091
However, he suspects
that something had gone wrong.

68
00:04:19,676 --> 00:04:22,053
That someone had sabotaged them,

69
00:04:22,136 --> 00:04:23,471
which was why everything
turned into chaos.

70
00:04:23,554 --> 00:04:24,389
‪[Teresa inhales]

71
00:04:25,223 --> 00:04:26,975
Believe me, Jamilah.

72
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:30,687
My son wants to correct his mistake.

73
00:04:35,858 --> 00:04:37,318
- There she is!
- Jamilah! Jamilah!

74
00:04:38,653 --> 00:04:39,946
- [Norhana] Jamilah!
- Auntie!

75
00:04:40,029 --> 00:04:41,239
[sobs] Jamilah!

76
00:04:41,322 --> 00:04:42,824
- [Jamilah] Auntie!
- [Norhana] Jamilah!

77
00:04:42,907 --> 00:04:44,742
- Jamilah…
- Oh, Auntie…

78
00:04:44,826 --> 00:04:47,328
[Norhana] I'm so glad you're safe!

79
00:04:47,412 --> 00:04:48,454
[Norhana sobbing]

80
00:04:48,538 --> 00:04:49,747
[softly] Are you okay? [sniffs]

81
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:52,125
- Uncle.
- [Omar] Jamilah…

82
00:04:52,208 --> 00:04:55,169
I'd never forgive myself
if something happened to you.

83
00:04:55,253 --> 00:04:57,380
How could I ever explain that
to your brother?

84
00:04:59,924 --> 00:05:00,758
‪[dramatic whoosh]

85
00:05:04,095 --> 00:05:05,513
‪[dramatic whoosh]

86
00:05:06,681 --> 00:05:09,642
[sighs] Uncle Omar, you don't have
to worry anymore.

87
00:05:10,601 --> 00:05:12,603
The important thing is that I'm safe.

88
00:05:12,687 --> 00:05:13,771
That we've been reunited.

89
00:05:13,855 --> 00:05:15,606
That I'm going home in one piece.

90
00:05:15,690 --> 00:05:16,524
‪[dramatic sting]

91
00:05:20,194 --> 00:05:23,156
[morose music continues]

92
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:44,886
- [officer 1] Go away!
- [reporter] One question, Agent Reyes!

93
00:05:44,969 --> 00:05:47,430
[reporter] Let me ask
Agent Reyes this one time!

94
00:05:47,513 --> 00:05:48,681
[crowd clamoring]

95
00:05:48,765 --> 00:05:50,308
[reporter] I just have one question!

96
00:05:51,225 --> 00:05:54,312
- [officer] You have to go now!
- [reporter] He's here! Agent Reyes!

97
00:05:54,896 --> 00:05:56,731
- Agent Reyes, a question!
- [tense music playing]

98
00:05:57,774 --> 00:05:59,776
Don't you ever lay
a finger on our brother!

99
00:05:59,859 --> 00:06:01,986
Or else, we'll make all of you pay!

100
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:05,031
- [overlapping chatter]
- [camera shutter clicking]

101
00:06:06,491 --> 00:06:07,992
[reporter] Agent Reyes!

102
00:06:08,076 --> 00:06:11,079
Agent Reyes, congratulations
on the successful rescue.

103
00:06:11,162 --> 00:06:13,748
What was the key to this operation?

104
00:06:13,831 --> 00:06:15,249
- [Azuelo] Agent Reyes!
- [officer 2] Make way!

105
00:06:17,251 --> 00:06:20,838
[in English] Agent Reyes, congratulations!

106
00:06:20,922 --> 00:06:23,883
[in English] Team Task Force Alpha
is back!

107
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:27,553
[crowd whooping, clapping]

108
00:06:49,283 --> 00:06:52,995
[music becomes unsettling]

109
00:07:00,711 --> 00:07:03,422
Our priority is the safety of civilians.

110
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:05,842
Our mission was a success

111
00:07:05,925 --> 00:07:08,010
thanks to the coordinated efforts
of the entire team.

112
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:10,638
As of this moment, everyone is safe

113
00:07:10,721 --> 00:07:13,599
and in the care of medical professionals.

114
00:07:14,183 --> 00:07:15,518
Agent Reyes, how were
you able to execute--

115
00:07:15,601 --> 00:07:17,228
[Azuelo] Agent Reyes.

116
00:07:17,311 --> 00:07:18,521
I'll take it over from here.

117
00:07:18,604 --> 00:07:21,065
- [tense music playing]
- [camera shutter clicking]

118
00:07:21,149 --> 00:07:22,817
First of all,

119
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:25,778
I would like to personally commend

120
00:07:25,862 --> 00:07:28,448
the new Task Force Alpha.

121
00:07:28,531 --> 00:07:30,575
[crowd clapping, whooping]

122
00:07:34,495 --> 00:07:36,831
And under my supervision,

123
00:07:36,914 --> 00:07:38,499
it has been proven once again

124
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:41,919
that they are the best

125
00:07:42,003 --> 00:07:44,839
and truly reliable, above all.

126
00:07:44,922 --> 00:07:47,675
- [tense music continues]
- [whooping, clapping]

127
00:07:47,758 --> 00:07:50,470
If not for them,

128
00:07:50,553 --> 00:07:55,516
our streets would be overrun
by heartless criminals,

129
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,310
like these two!

130
00:07:57,393 --> 00:07:59,145
- [woman] That's right!
- [man] Lock them up!

131
00:07:59,228 --> 00:08:02,231
- [woman] Put them behind bars!
- [man] Make an example out of them!

132
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:04,567
[suspenseful music playing]

133
00:08:09,405 --> 00:08:14,243
[Azuelo] This was a successful operation
by Task Force Alpha

134
00:08:14,327 --> 00:08:16,704
under the SID.

135
00:08:16,787 --> 00:08:19,248
After a long time,

136
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:25,213
we finally captured the Rosales Brothers.

137
00:08:25,296 --> 00:08:29,967
- [crowd whooping, clapping]
- [camera shutter clicking]

138
00:08:32,887 --> 00:08:35,640
They will lead us

139
00:08:36,307 --> 00:08:39,519
to the syndicates that supply them

140
00:08:39,602 --> 00:08:42,104
with high-powered firearms.

141
00:08:42,188 --> 00:08:43,564
[gunshot]

142
00:08:43,648 --> 00:08:44,607
- [crowd screaming]
- [officer] Get down!

143
00:08:44,690 --> 00:08:45,733
[gunshot]

144
00:08:45,816 --> 00:08:48,986
- [thrilling music playing]
- [crowd screaming]

145
00:08:50,905 --> 00:08:52,990
[crowd clamoring]

146
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:54,951
[officer shouts]

147
00:08:55,826 --> 00:08:57,912
- [officer 1] Stay out of sight!
- [officer 2] Keep your heads low!

148
00:08:57,995 --> 00:08:59,622
[crowd clamoring]

149
00:08:59,705 --> 00:09:00,540
‪[music intensifying]

150
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:03,918
‪[tense dramatic music playing]

151
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:13,511
[gun cocking]

152
00:09:15,304 --> 00:09:17,598
- [overlapping shouting]
- [suspenseful music playing]

153
00:09:17,682 --> 00:09:18,766
Stay low!

154
00:09:18,849 --> 00:09:20,226
[in English] Stand down!

155
00:09:20,309 --> 00:09:21,519
- [Lara] Please, calm down!
- [Marcus, in English] Take cover!

156
00:09:25,147 --> 00:09:25,982
‪[tinkling]

157
00:09:57,555 --> 00:09:58,848
[cartridge case clinks]

158
00:10:17,575 --> 00:10:18,743
[in English] Search the area.

159
00:10:20,036 --> 00:10:21,912
Look for evidence.

160
00:10:21,996 --> 00:10:24,415
Shell casings, anything at all.

161
00:10:25,875 --> 00:10:26,917
[in English] Move!

162
00:10:31,881 --> 00:10:33,799
[thrilling music playing]

163
00:10:37,845 --> 00:10:39,013
Go check there.

164
00:10:39,096 --> 00:10:40,306
‪[suspenseful music playing]

165
00:10:53,235 --> 00:10:55,237
[grunting and groaning]

166
00:10:57,323 --> 00:11:00,951
[tense music playing]

167
00:11:01,035 --> 00:11:01,869
‪[grunting and groaning]

168
00:11:04,747 --> 00:11:05,581
‪[Lara grunts]

169
00:11:09,627 --> 00:11:10,836
[thug grunts]

170
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:12,254
- [sighs]
- [neck cracks]

171
00:11:12,963 --> 00:11:14,590
‪[grunting and groaning]

172
00:11:22,598 --> 00:11:23,891
[panting]

173
00:11:24,683 --> 00:11:25,518
‪[heaves]

174
00:11:27,937 --> 00:11:28,771
‪[sharp inhale]

175
00:11:38,572 --> 00:11:40,950
[sinister music playing]

176
00:12:01,846 --> 00:12:03,097
Montes.

177
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:05,641
What are you doing?

178
00:12:05,724 --> 00:12:08,060
Tying my shoes. Obviously.

179
00:12:09,770 --> 00:12:12,106
Can’t a man tie his shoes peacefully?

180
00:12:12,189 --> 00:12:13,983
What? You miss me already?

181
00:12:14,066 --> 00:12:18,112
[tense music playing]

182
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:27,121
[Marcus] <i>They killed the suspects,</i>

183
00:12:27,204 --> 00:12:29,331
<i>so they couldn't reveal</i>
<i>where they got their weapons.</i>

184
00:12:29,874 --> 00:12:31,333
<i>That means…</i>

185
00:12:31,417 --> 00:12:33,419
[tense music continues]

186
00:12:35,254 --> 00:12:36,672
[in English] Listen up, all units.

187
00:12:37,756 --> 00:12:39,633
[in English] Target priority.

188
00:12:39,717 --> 00:12:42,720
Protect the remaining suspect
in the hospital.

189
00:12:42,803 --> 00:12:45,347
Tommy Rosales is in danger.

190
00:12:45,431 --> 00:12:47,725
I repeat, protect the suspect.

191
00:12:47,808 --> 00:12:49,310
[in English] Roger, sir.

192
00:12:50,144 --> 00:12:51,645
[in English] Copy.

193
00:12:51,729 --> 00:12:52,646
Come on.

194
00:12:54,023 --> 00:12:55,774
[tense music continues]

195
00:12:59,778 --> 00:13:00,821
[in English] Move!

196
00:13:04,158 --> 00:13:04,992
‪[sniffles]

197
00:13:07,912 --> 00:13:09,580
[whistles]

198
00:13:16,545 --> 00:13:18,297
[Tommy grunts, exhales]

199
00:13:18,380 --> 00:13:19,215
‪[music intensifies]

200
00:13:19,423 --> 00:13:20,257
‪[twinkle]

201
00:13:20,925 --> 00:13:24,136
[ominous music playing]

202
00:13:48,035 --> 00:13:49,036
- Hey!
- Back off!

203
00:13:49,119 --> 00:13:50,454
- [officer] Take it easy, sir!
- [Tommy sobs]

204
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:54,833
Sir, the suspect is secure.

205
00:13:55,709 --> 00:13:57,753
All threats have been neutralized.

206
00:13:57,836 --> 00:13:58,879
We're good.

207
00:13:58,963 --> 00:14:00,673
- [officer] Sir, please calm down.
- Sir!

208
00:14:00,756 --> 00:14:02,091
- [officer] Put the gun down.
- [people clamoring]

209
00:14:02,174 --> 00:14:05,636
[tense music playing]

210
00:14:06,303 --> 00:14:08,639
- [gun fires]
- [people screaming]

211
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:10,766
[officer] What happened?!

212
00:14:10,849 --> 00:14:14,103
- [screaming continues]
- [tense music continues]

213
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:22,403
- [people clamoring]
- [sinister music playing]

214
00:14:28,576 --> 00:14:30,077
[clamoring continues]

215
00:14:36,125 --> 00:14:37,126
[gasps]

216
00:14:38,168 --> 00:14:39,712
[Marcus] What happened?!

217
00:14:41,130 --> 00:14:43,549
Sir, he grabbed my gun and shot himself!

218
00:14:43,632 --> 00:14:45,926
- [man] Why would he do that?
- [people clamoring]

219
00:14:50,556 --> 00:14:53,726
[sinister music continues]

220
00:14:53,809 --> 00:14:55,394
- [man screams]
- [people clamoring]

221
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:57,813
[woman speaks indistinctly]

222
00:14:58,522 --> 00:14:59,356
‪[man gasps]

223
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:04,904
What's up, brother?

224
00:15:07,990 --> 00:15:10,200
Bro, I need to speak to the other suspect.

225
00:15:10,284 --> 00:15:11,452
[in English] Copy, sir.

226
00:15:16,206 --> 00:15:18,167
- [cop] Sir!
- [Felix] Step outside.

227
00:15:20,794 --> 00:15:21,629
‪[Felix sighs]

228
00:15:25,966 --> 00:15:28,427
Did you hear the gunshots outside?

229
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:30,429
Those were for your brothers.

230
00:15:31,555 --> 00:15:32,598
Mm?

231
00:15:33,599 --> 00:15:36,477
Now, I'll give you a choice.

232
00:15:37,061 --> 00:15:39,980
Either I kill your mother…

233
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:42,650
or you kill yourself.

234
00:15:44,401 --> 00:15:45,527
Hmm?

235
00:15:45,611 --> 00:15:47,613
[grim music playing]

236
00:15:49,698 --> 00:15:51,909
Choose wisely, kid.

237
00:15:51,992 --> 00:15:52,826
‪[Felix chuckles]

238
00:15:55,162 --> 00:15:56,080
[dramatic sting]

239
00:15:57,456 --> 00:15:58,290
‪[dramatic sting]

240
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:04,004
‪[dramatic sting]

241
00:16:07,132 --> 00:16:09,009
[TV reporter] <i>Breaking news.</i>

242
00:16:09,093 --> 00:16:11,387
<i>We have confirmation</i>
<i>that Tommy Rosales is dead</i>

243
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:13,597
<i>following an apparent</i>
<i>self-inflicted gunshot wound.</i>

244
00:16:13,681 --> 00:16:17,726
<i>This happened moments after</i>
<i>an unidentified suspect</i>

245
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:22,272
<i>shot and killed his two brothers,</i>
<i>Axl and Jovi Rosales.</i>

246
00:16:22,356 --> 00:16:23,899
No! [sobs]

247
00:16:23,983 --> 00:16:25,567
Axl!

248
00:16:26,902 --> 00:16:28,821
Jovi! Tommy!

249
00:16:28,904 --> 00:16:31,031
[morose music playing]

250
00:16:32,908 --> 00:16:37,287
[wailing]

251
00:16:37,371 --> 00:16:38,622
‪[tense morose music playing]

252
00:16:46,296 --> 00:16:50,426
[mother] My children! [wails]

253
00:16:57,266 --> 00:16:59,059
[in English] This is outrageous!

254
00:16:59,143 --> 00:17:03,647
Those crooks were supposed
to lead us to their supplier

255
00:17:03,731 --> 00:17:07,234
of high-powered firearms!

256
00:17:07,317 --> 00:17:09,445
And now you're telling me
that their brother,

257
00:17:09,528 --> 00:17:12,448
the only surviving suspect,

258
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:14,199
- committed suicide?!
- [slams table]

259
00:17:15,492 --> 00:17:17,036
[in English] Goddammit!

260
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:20,789
Sir, this means they fear
the syndicate more than us.

261
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:23,834
[in English] Sir, I'm sorry.

262
00:17:24,543 --> 00:17:26,628
I don't know how this happened.
I should've seen it coming.

263
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:28,464
The brothers were calculated.

264
00:17:29,131 --> 00:17:30,507
Sir, there is no one to blame.

265
00:17:30,591 --> 00:17:32,551
[in English] That's the point!

266
00:17:34,178 --> 00:17:35,971
It is unacceptable
that they outsmarted us!

267
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:39,266
You should've been one step ahead of them!

268
00:17:44,104 --> 00:17:45,606
With all due respect, sir,

269
00:17:46,732 --> 00:17:49,109
we shouldn't have faced
the press right away.

270
00:17:50,694 --> 00:17:51,862
What did you say?

271
00:17:52,529 --> 00:17:54,990
- Are you asking to be suspended?!
- What do you think, sir?

272
00:17:55,074 --> 00:17:57,326
[unsettling music playing]

273
00:17:57,409 --> 00:17:59,745
Have you learned nothing?
We keep messing up.

274
00:17:59,828 --> 00:18:01,663
We're a laughing stock!

275
00:18:02,289 --> 00:18:04,625
All our hard work is for nothing.

276
00:18:04,708 --> 00:18:07,294
Is this all just damage control for TFA?

277
00:18:08,670 --> 00:18:10,506
Our friends died.

278
00:18:11,090 --> 00:18:12,758
We replaced them!

279
00:18:14,510 --> 00:18:15,761
But why has nothing changed?

280
00:18:15,844 --> 00:18:18,097
Suarez, enough.

281
00:18:18,180 --> 00:18:20,015
- Enough.
- [Felix] Don't worry.

282
00:18:20,099 --> 00:18:22,059
We'll get back at them eventually.

283
00:18:22,142 --> 00:18:24,478
This isn't over.

284
00:18:24,561 --> 00:18:25,729
Right?!

285
00:18:27,314 --> 00:18:28,148
Right?

286
00:18:35,322 --> 00:18:36,156
‪[music intensifies]

287
00:18:38,325 --> 00:18:39,993
- Sir.
- [door slams shut]

288
00:18:41,620 --> 00:18:42,454
‪[door creaks open]

289
00:18:50,254 --> 00:18:53,006
Sir, the sniper left this behind.

290
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:56,093
I hid it before someone could find it.

291
00:18:56,176 --> 00:18:57,302
Don't worry.

292
00:18:57,386 --> 00:18:59,346
No one saw me.

293
00:18:59,429 --> 00:19:00,722
[in English] Good job.

294
00:19:01,557 --> 00:19:05,394
Sir, why was the leader
of those crooks killed?

295
00:19:05,477 --> 00:19:07,146
What's going on?

296
00:19:07,229 --> 00:19:12,192
[tense music playing]

297
00:19:12,276 --> 00:19:13,861
Why are you asking so many questions?

298
00:19:15,445 --> 00:19:16,530
It's none of your business.

299
00:19:17,698 --> 00:19:19,241
Yes, sir. I'm sorry.

300
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:22,661
[tapping]

301
00:19:24,872 --> 00:19:29,126
[music intensifies]

302
00:19:31,461 --> 00:19:34,882
[Ahmad] <i>This bank robbery</i>
<i>that escalated into a hostage situation,</i>

303
00:19:36,049 --> 00:19:38,260
<i>it wasn't a random incident.</i>

304
00:19:38,886 --> 00:19:42,639
<i>Those brothers wouldn’t</i>
<i>have been silenced like that</i>

305
00:19:42,723 --> 00:19:45,017
<i>if this was just an ordinary crime.</i>

306
00:19:45,976 --> 00:19:49,062
Oh my goodness, Mama Loi.
This is too much to handle.

307
00:19:49,146 --> 00:19:53,400
- [Loi] What happened, Mother?
- It's the NLEA and SID, Mama Loi!

308
00:19:53,483 --> 00:19:58,614
There was a hostage-taking
at S. Trinidad Hospital!

309
00:19:58,697 --> 00:20:00,324
- It's all over social media!
- [brooding music playing]

310
00:20:00,407 --> 00:20:02,367
- [man] Right?
- It was that group…

311
00:20:02,451 --> 00:20:04,411
- Metal-13!
- [man] Metal-13.

312
00:20:04,494 --> 00:20:05,787
They may be ordinary criminals,

313
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:09,458
but they were carrying
high-powered weapons!

314
00:20:09,541 --> 00:20:10,834
- Oh my gosh!
- [man] Yes!

315
00:20:10,918 --> 00:20:12,586
They had big guns?

316
00:20:12,669 --> 00:20:16,882
Everyone thought
the mission was a success,

317
00:20:16,965 --> 00:20:18,300
but it was far from over.

318
00:20:18,383 --> 00:20:22,930
Maybe Task Force Alpha's
so-called rescue mission

319
00:20:23,013 --> 00:20:23,972
was just staged.

320
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:27,059
<i>Someone is definitely</i>
<i>pulling the strings here!</i>

321
00:20:27,142 --> 00:20:29,061
Our country is still in danger

322
00:20:29,144 --> 00:20:32,439
because of the spread
of these high-powered firearms

323
00:20:32,522 --> 00:20:35,734
that we still don't know
where they're coming from.

324
00:20:35,817 --> 00:20:37,945
- So many people have died.
- [woman] Yes.

325
00:20:38,028 --> 00:20:43,158
Those people have families,
for Christ's sake!

326
00:20:43,242 --> 00:20:46,662
<i>I wonder, who shot those crooks?</i>

327
00:20:46,745 --> 00:20:48,413
<i>Why were they killed?</i>

328
00:20:48,497 --> 00:20:51,500
Are you sure you can
handle this, Task Force Alpha?

329
00:20:52,376 --> 00:20:54,336
Just resign if you can't!

330
00:20:54,419 --> 00:20:57,839
Wherever these weapons are coming from,

331
00:20:57,923 --> 00:21:00,884
the authorities must trace them
and put a stop to it.

332
00:21:00,968 --> 00:21:04,388
Our countrymen have suffered enough!

333
00:21:04,471 --> 00:21:06,181
- Amen to that!
- Amen!

334
00:21:06,265 --> 00:21:08,308
I hope both parties can reconcile.

335
00:21:08,392 --> 00:21:11,687
- Then be the mediator!
- No, I don't want to!

336
00:21:12,271 --> 00:21:13,397
- [notification sound]
- [netizen 1] <i>It was staged!</i>

337
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:16,066
<i>Those hostage-takers</i>
<i>were killed to hide the truth.</i>

338
00:21:16,149 --> 00:21:17,442
<i>This has a cover-up written all over it!</i>

339
00:21:17,526 --> 00:21:18,443
[notification sound]

340
00:21:18,527 --> 00:21:20,362
[netizen 2] <i>Are we really safe?</i>

341
00:21:20,445 --> 00:21:22,990
<i>High-powered guns in the hands of crooks?</i>

342
00:21:23,073 --> 00:21:24,741
<i>A sniper in front of a hospital?</i>

343
00:21:25,325 --> 00:21:26,785
<i>What the hell, Philippines?</i>

344
00:21:29,496 --> 00:21:30,998
[in English] Goddammit!

345
00:21:31,081 --> 00:21:32,040
‪[thudding]

346
00:21:32,124 --> 00:21:32,958
[notification sound]

347
00:21:34,334 --> 00:21:38,213
[netizen 3] <i>Task Force Alpha?</i>
<i>More like Task Force Idiots.</i>

348
00:21:38,297 --> 00:21:40,173
[netizen 4] <i>TFA is just a PR stunt.</i>

349
00:21:40,257 --> 00:21:43,218
<i>We need real protection.</i>
<i>Not just photos and poses.</i>

350
00:21:44,052 --> 00:21:46,722
[netizen 5] <i>Photos like this?</i> [laughs]

351
00:21:46,805 --> 00:21:48,098
[grunts angrily]

352
00:21:48,181 --> 00:21:51,310
- [tense music playing]
- [huffs]

353
00:21:51,393 --> 00:21:52,227
‪[music intensifies]

354
00:22:05,365 --> 00:22:08,118
[Ahmad] <i>Someone is orchestrating this.</i>

355
00:22:13,373 --> 00:22:17,377
<i>They’re deliberately causing trouble.</i>

356
00:22:22,799 --> 00:22:24,718
<i>Is this a destabilization attempt?</i>

357
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:32,684
[Marcus] A lot of people have died!

358
00:22:32,768 --> 00:22:36,480
And more will die
if you don’t tell me the truth.

359
00:22:36,563 --> 00:22:38,273
I don't have anything to do with that!

360
00:22:38,356 --> 00:22:40,442
I'm not a part of the syndicate!

361
00:22:40,525 --> 00:22:42,861
[Marcus] <i>I thought you wanted</i>
<i>to get justice for your people.</i>

362
00:22:42,944 --> 00:22:43,904
<i>This is your chance.</i>

363
00:22:43,987 --> 00:22:45,781
Tell me what you know.

364
00:22:45,864 --> 00:22:47,616
[Felix] <i>Madam Lara is confused.</i>

365
00:22:47,699 --> 00:22:51,870
<i>She hasn't realized</i>
<i>that the General is right.</i>

366
00:22:51,953 --> 00:22:53,747
[boy] <i>Why won't you leave me alone?!</i>

367
00:22:54,539 --> 00:22:55,957
[man] <i>You're an embarrassment! Go home!</i>

368
00:22:56,041 --> 00:22:59,211
[Felix] <i>He will learn to love us one day.</i>

369
00:22:59,294 --> 00:23:01,797
<i>I cleaned it already. Are we good?</i>

370
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:03,882
[in English] Shut up! Get out of my face!

371
00:23:03,965 --> 00:23:06,218
I'm just doing my job, Lara.

372
00:23:06,301 --> 00:23:09,638
Don't forget how important our mission is.

373
00:23:10,889 --> 00:23:14,684
[reporter] <i>There are strict policies</i>
<i>on gun ownership.</i>

374
00:23:14,768 --> 00:23:17,521
So who is supplying these weapons?

375
00:23:17,604 --> 00:23:20,440
[woman] <i>Crime is on the rise today.</i>

376
00:23:20,524 --> 00:23:23,819
[Norhana] <i>I pray that Jalil</i>
<i>and Jamilah are always safe.</i>
